bug.short_desc: Latest Chromium update breaks HiDPI support
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem:
HiDPI support broken (tabs, menus, content extremely small)
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
chromium-52.0.2743.116-1.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible:
Always (on my machine at least)
Steps to Reproduce:
1. Upgrade from chromium-52.0.2743.116-1.fc24.x86_64 2. Launch chromium-browser 3. Get a magnifying glass
Actual results:
Chromium application windows are hard to read and interact with
Expected results:
Chromium application windows are scaled similar to other applications
Additional info:
Verified that downgrading to chromium-52.0.2743.116-1.fc24.x86_64 and chromium-52.0.2743.116-1.fc24.x86_64 resolves the issue. Guessing it's related to the note about enabling hidpi support, which may have actually broken hidpi support?

Apparently my copy / paste skills aren't working well today. What I *meant* to say under additional info is that downgrading to chromium-52.0.2743.82-9.fc24.x86_64.rpm and chromium-libs-52.0.2743.82-9.fc24.x86_64.rpm results in working hidpi support.
I don't have a HiDPI monitor, but I'll do a build with enable_hidpi=0 so you can test it and see if things go back to normal.
